      "heading": "Introduction",
      "text": "The Journal of Symbolic Logic is a peer-reviewed mathematics journal published quarterly by Association for Symbolic Logic . It was established in 1936 and covers mathematical logic . The journal is indexed by Mathematical Reviews , Zentralblatt MATH , and Scopus . Its 2009 MCQ was 0.28, and its 2009 impact factor was 0.631."
